Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.05,0:01:15.62,辉注,,0,0,0,,Valsalva动作：捏住鼻子用力呼气
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.48,0:01:55.42,辉注,,0,0,0,,@shifte_mir：你要训练多少小时？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.70,0:02:36.09,辉注,,0,0,0,,@rose._.valade：太空行走训练时你第一反应是怎样的？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.48,0:03:00.95,辉注,,0,0,0,,@grajohnt: 我有个朋友问我 能不能写信 别给我发拒绝我的电子邮件？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.82,0:03:11.60,辉注,,0,0,0,,@marissasayr：这份工作带给你最好的经历是什么？
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.59,0:00:02.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,大家好 我叫Jasmin Moghbeli
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.59,0:00:02.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Hi, I'm Jasmin Moghbeli.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:02.06,0:00:05.54,辉中,,0,0,0,,我是NASA的宇航员 这里是“#AskNASA”栏目
Dialogue: 2,0:00:02.06,0:00:05.54,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm a NASA astronaut and this is #AskNASA.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:10.60,0:00:16.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,NASA打算在3月2日到3月31日期间招募更多宇航员
Dialogue: 2,0:00:10.60,0:00:16.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,NASA will be opening its applications for more astronauts on March 2nd through March 31st.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:16.30,0:00:19.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们收到了很多相关的问题
Dialogue: 2,0:00:16.30,0:00:19.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we've got a bunch of questions related to that.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:19.16,0:00:21.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,这个在线评估是关于什么的？
Dialogue: 2,0:00:19.16,0:00:21.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,What is this online assessment about?
Dialogue: 1,0:00:21.86,0:00:25.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,它会测试你的天赋与技能水平
Dialogue: 2,0:00:21.86,0:00:25.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's testing things like your aptitude and skills
Dialogue: 1,0:00:25.50,0:00:30.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,从而保证你在整个流程早期你就有成为NASA宇航员所需要的的资质
Dialogue: 2,0:00:25.50,0:00:30.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,to make sure earlier in the process that you have what it takes to be a NASA astronaut.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:30.58,0:00:33.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,好 下一个问题
Dialogue: 2,0:00:30.58,0:00:33.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's move on to our next question.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:33.44,0:00:35.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,哪些学位不算数？
Dialogue: 2,0:00:33.44,0:00:35.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,What degrees don't count?
Dialogue: 1,0:00:36.16,0:00:39.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,我想从正面来回答 哪些学位是符合要求的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:36.16,0:00:39.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,So I like to be positive and start with what degrees do count.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:39.74,0:00:42.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,你需要获得研究生的学位
Dialogue: 2,0:00:39.74,0:00:42.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, you do need a master's degree.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:42.92,0:00:44.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,谢谢！
Dialogue: 2,0:00:42.92,0:00:44.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 1,0:00:44.38,0:00:50.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,而且需要是STEM学科的研究生学位 即科学、技术、工程或者数学
Dialogue: 2,0:00:44.38,0:00:50.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,You need a master's degree in a STEM field so Science, Technology, Engineering or Mathematics.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:50.43,0:00:55.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,有些学位是不行的 比如护理学 心理学
Dialogue: 2,0:00:50.43,0:00:55.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,There are certain degrees in there that don't count such as nursing, psychology,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:55.44,0:00:58.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,运动生理学或社会科学
Dialogue: 2,0:00:55.44,0:00:58.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,exercise physiology or social sciences,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:58.69,0:01:03.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,具体细节请前往nasa.gov/astronauts
Dialogue: 2,0:00:58.69,0:01:03.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,but for details on that you can go to nasa.gov/astronauts.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:05.12,0:01:08.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,你面试时被问到的最奇怪的问题是什么？
Dialogue: 2,0:01:05.12,0:01:08.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,What was the weirdest question you got during your interview?
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.05,0:01:15.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,我面试时一个耳科医生问我能否做一个Valsalva动作
Dialogue: 2,0:01:10.05,0:01:15.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, when I went to see the ear doctor in the interview, and he asked if I could do a Valsalva Maneuver.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:16.66,0:01:21.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,你们坐飞机的时候可能也做过这个动作
Dialogue: 2,0:01:16.66,0:01:21.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,You may be familiar with that from flying in commercial aircraft.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:21.07,0:01:25.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,反正我做完之后 他说我的Valsalva动作非常标准
Dialogue: 2,0:01:21.07,0:01:25.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,Anyway, afterwords he told me I did textbook Valsalva.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:25.82,0:01:26.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,完美
Dialogue: 2,0:01:25.82,0:01:26.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,Shoo in.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:26.96,0:01:27.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,下一个问题
Dialogue: 2,0:01:26.96,0:01:27.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,Next question.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:29.02,0:01:32.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,成为阿尔忒弥斯计划的宇航员之一 你最激动的是什么？
Dialogue: 2,0:01:29.02,0:01:32.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,What are you most excited about for being a part of the Artemis generation?
Dialogue: 1,0:01:34.02,0:01:34.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,哇！
Dialogue: 2,0:01:34.02,0:01:34.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 1,0:01:34.88,0:01:36.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,这可有的聊了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:34.88,0:01:36.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,I could go on about that one for a while.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:36.84,0:01:40.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,首先 我们到现在还没去过别的星球
Dialogue: 2,0:01:36.84,0:01:40.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,First off, we haven't stepped on another planetary body in my lifetime.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:40.83,0:01:45.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以如果我认识的某个人踏上了月球 我会非常激动
Dialogue: 2,0:01:40.83,0:01:45.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, it will be super exciting to see someone I know stepping on the surface of the Moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:45.64,0:01:48.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,同时 这也使我们为未来的任务做进一步的准备
Dialogue: 2,0:01:45.64,0:01:48.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,But also, how that sets us up for future missions
Dialogue: 1,0:01:48.34,0:01:52.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,让我们在太阳系中走得更远 比如去火星
Dialogue: 2,0:01:48.34,0:01:52.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,to go farther than we have ever gone in our solar system before, on to Mars.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.48,0:01:55.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们现在一直在训练
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.48,0:01:55.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we're constantly working on training.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:55.33,0:01:57.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们前两年纯粹都是训练
Dialogue: 2,0:01:55.33,0:01:57.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Our first two years were purely training.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:57.76,0:02:01.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,明天我要去中性浮力实验室练习太空行走
Dialogue: 2,0:01:57.76,0:02:01.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow I'm getting in the neutral buoyancy lab to practice a spacewalk.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:01.39,0:02:05.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,周五我还要上T-38飞机 所以这是个日复一日的持续的过程
Dialogue: 2,0:02:01.39,0:02:05.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,Friday I'm getting in a T-38, so it's a continuous process every day.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:05.65,0:02:08.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,好 我们看下一个问题
Dialogue: 2,0:02:05.65,0:02:08.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,Here, let's move on to our next question.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:08.32,0:02:11.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,为何宇航员要通过体检？
Dialogue: 2,0:02:08.32,0:02:11.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why do astronauts need to pass a physical?
Dialogue: 1,0:02:11.90,0:02:16.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,实际上宇航员在训练的时候会涉及到很多身体有关的内容
Dialogue: 2,0:02:11.90,0:02:16.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, there are actually lots of physical aspects to our astronaut training
Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.19,0:02:20.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,从我过去两年持续的训练中我就能亲身感受到这一点
Dialogue: 2,0:02:16.19,0:02:20.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I can tell you that from the last two years I've constantly been working out.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:20.14,0:02:23.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,而你将来要进行太空行走
Dialogue: 2,0:02:20.14,0:02:23.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,But you need to be able to one, do the spacewalks.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:23.44,0:02:27.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,你还要能坐火箭发射到太空 还要能开喷气机
Dialogue: 2,0:02:23.44,0:02:27.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,You also need to be able to launch to space, fly in jets,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:27.13,0:02:30.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以NASA希望我们每个人都能有最好的身体条件
Dialogue: 2,0:02:27.13,0:02:30.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,so we need to make sure everyone is in their best physical condition.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.70,0:02:36.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,我第一次穿上舱外宇航服的时候 我发现这比我想得要难得多
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.70,0:02:36.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,Well the first time I got in the suit, it was a lot harder than I thought it was going to be.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:36.09,0:02:41.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,你要在整件宇航服内工作 它就是你的小型飞船 真的非常累
Dialogue: 2,0:02:36.09,0:02:41.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,You're working within this whole spacesuit, it's really your own spacecraft and it's really tiring.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:41.97,0:02:44.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空“行走”用的是手 而不是脚
Dialogue: 2,0:02:41.97,0:02:44.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,You walk with your hands, not your feet.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:44.32,0:02:46.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,你做的每件事都会让你发现自己比平常要大上一圈
Dialogue: 2,0:02:44.32,0:02:46.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,Everything you do, you're much bigger than you expect to be
Dialogue: 1,0:02:46.96,0:02:49.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以你要确保不要碰到别的东西
Dialogue: 2,0:02:46.96,0:02:49.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,so you have to make sure you're not running into things.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:49.01,0:02:52.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,我第一想法就是感觉 太爽了 但也太难了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:49.01,0:02:52.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,My first thought was, this is awesome, but this it's also really hard.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:54.67,0:03:01.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,告诉你的“朋友” 我们NASA是很爱护地球的 我们不想浪费纸张
Dialogue: 2,0:02:54.67,0:03:01.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,Well, tell your "friend" that at NASA we really like the planet Earth and we don't wanna waste all that paper.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:01.95,0:03:06.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们上次收到了8000份申请 所以我们可能还是用电子邮件
Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.95,0:03:06.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,We had over eighteen thousand applications last time so, we'll probably stick with emails.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:06.82,0:03:11.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,我目前为止最好的经历就是遇见了在这里工作的其他人
Dialogue: 2,0:03:06.82,0:03:11.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,My best experience, by far, has been meeting the other people that work here.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:11.36,0:03:16.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,不止是其他宇航员 还有在任务中心工作的工程师
Dialogue: 2,0:03:11.36,0:03:16.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,Not just the other astronauts, but the engineers, those that work in Mission Control,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:16.30,0:03:18.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,每天为我们提供支持的所有人
Dialogue: 2,0:03:16.30,0:03:18.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,all the support personnel that help us every day.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:18.80,0:03:20.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,比如在中性浮力实验室的潜水员们
Dialogue: 2,0:03:18.80,0:03:20.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,The divers at the Neutral Buoyancy Lab.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.80,0:03:26.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,在约翰逊太空中心和所有其他NASA中心 每天都有很多人为我们提供支持
Dialogue: 2,0:03:20.80,0:03:26.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,We've got so many people here at Johnson Space Center and all the other NASA centers supporting us every day.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:27.06,0:03:28.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,嗯 这就是我们所有的问题
Dialogue: 2,0:03:27.06,0:03:28.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,All right, that's all our questions.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:29.52,0:03:30.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,完美！
Dialogue: 2,0:03:29.52,0:03:30.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,Perfect!
Dialogue: 1,0:03:42.38,0:03:43.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,你有什么问题想问NASA吗？
Dialogue: 2,0:03:42.38,0:03:43.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,Do you have a question for NASA?
Dialogue: 1,0:03:44.26,0:03:49.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,欢迎在推特上加上“#AskNASA ”标签将您的问题发送给我们的专家
Dialogue: 2,0:03:44.26,0:03:49.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,Send your questions to our experts on Twitter using #AskNASA.
